From 7ac19528012887324280feb7c292107b73428f9a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
Date: Tue, 27 Jan 2026 23:48:29 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: add HPE GXP UMAC driver

Add the ethernet MAC driver for the HPE GXP BMC SoC used in ProLiant
Gen10/Gen11 servers. The UMAC controller provides:

- Standard MII PHY support via phylib with Marvell 88E1514 fixup
- NCSI support for sideband management through host NIC
- NAPI for interrupt mitigation
- Standard ethtool operations

The GXP includes two UMAC instances - one for dedicated BMC management
connected to an external PHY, and one for NCSI communication.

Co-developed-by: Jean-Marie Verdun <jean-marie.verdun@hpe.com>
Signed-off-by: Jean-Marie Verdun <jean-marie.verdun@hpe.com>
Co-developed-by: Michal Gorlas <michal.gorlas@9elements.com>
Signed-off-by: Michal Gorlas <michal.gorlas@9elements.com>
Signed-off-by: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
